      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent GCI analysis demonstrating discretization error below 5% for hemolysis-relevant shear stress QoIs; Gradation 3 required.",
      "rationale": "A three-mesh refinement study was conducted (coarse 4.1 M, medium 8.7 M, fine 17.2 M cells). GCI values for volume-averaged shear stress converged at approximately 8.3%, exceeding the 5% threshold. The team attributed the residual error to near-impeller boundary layer resolution constraints and elected to proceed, classifying the achieved level as Gradation 2. The shortfall relative to the Gradation 3 requirement was documented in the assessment record but was not treated as a blocking finding; the decision record records the package as Accepted without remediation or a compensating measure. This constitutes an unresolved factor shortfall under an Accepted outcome."
    },
